The paper deals with a problem related to graph distances and their emulation, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms. The use of planar graphs is also a significant aspect of the paper, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.DM (discrete mathematics). The paper also involves computational complexity and optimization, which could lead to categories such as cs.NA (numerical analysis) and cs.GT (computer science and game theory).
